data.value: WARNING: The 'PartitionOwnershipExpirationInterval' and 'LoadBalancingUpdateInterval' are configured for intervals that may cause stability issues with partition ownership. It is recommended that the 'PartitionOwnershipExpirationInterval' be at least 3 times greater than the 'LoadBalancingUpdateInterval' and very strongly advised that it should be no less than twice as long. When these intervals are too close together, ownership may expire before it is renewed during load balancing which will cause partitions to migrate. Consider adjusting the intervals in the processor options if you experience issues. Load Balancing Interval '{0:0:00}' seconds. Partition Ownership Interval '{1:0:00}' seconds.
